      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__conn__mgr__connectivity_1gaa79794ce9c773c0c3932121c931ac2d6" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int conn_mgr_if_get_opt</definition>
        <argsstring>(struct net_if *iface, int optname, void *optval, size_t *optlen)</argsstring>
        <name>conn_mgr_if_get_opt</name>
        <param>
          <type>struct <ref refid="structnet__if" kindref="compound">net_if</ref> *</type>
          <declname>iface</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>optname</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>void *</type>
          <declname>optval</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="retained__mem_8h_1a36713c339c3c5ec6d6bd481480bdb6f9" kindref="member">size_t</ref> *</type>
          <declname>optlen</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Get implementation-specific connectivity options. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If the provided iface has been bound to a connectivity implementation that supports it, retrieves implementation-specific connectivity options related to the iface.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>iface</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the network interface. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>optname</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Integer value representing the option to set. The meaning of values is up to the <ref refid="structconn__mgr__conn__api" kindref="compound">conn_mgr_conn_api</ref> implementation. Some settings may be shared by multiple ifaces. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>optval</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to where the retrieved value should be stored. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>optlen</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to length (in bytes) of the destination buffer available for storing the retrieved value. If the available space is less than what is needed, -ENOBUFS is returned. If the available space is invalid, -EINVAL is returned.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
optlen will always be set to the total number of bytes written, regardless of whether an error is returned, even if zero bytes were written.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>0</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if successful. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-ENOTSUP</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if conn_mgr_if_get_opt is not implemented by the iface. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-ENOBUFS</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if retrieval buffer is too small. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-EINVAL</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if invalid retrieval buffer length is provided, or if NULL optval or optlen pointer provided. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-ENOPROTOOPT</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if the optname is not recognized. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>implementation-specific error code otherwise. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
